India Bank Loans Rose 294.3 Bln Rupees in Two Weeks to Sept 9

-- B y   V   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-09-23T11:32:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/india-bank-loans-rose-294-3-bln-rupees-in-two-weeks-to-sept-9.html
Indian banksâ€™ loans rose by 294.3
billion rupees ($6 billion) in the two weeks ended Sept. 9,
raising outstanding advances to 40.7 trillion rupees, according
to central bank data.  Loans to industry and consumers increased 296 billion
rupees during the period, while food credit decreased 1.65
billion rupees, the Reserve Bank of India said in an e-mailed
statement.  Credit rose by 20.4 percent, or by 6.91 trillion rupees, in
the 12 months through Sept. 9, according to the statement. Total
bank deposits rose by 17.5 percent, or 8.24 trillion rupees, in
the same period to 55.2 trillion rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
